        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Problem 1. Suppose that a sequence "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\{ X _ { n } \\}"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "of real-valued random variables converges to "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "X"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "in distribution and there are positive constants "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "r"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "and "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "C"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "such that "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\mathbb { E } | X _ { n } | ^ { r } \\leq C"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "for all "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "n"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ". Show that "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                111,
                204,
                883,
                238
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "equation_interline",
            "content": {
                "math_content": "\\lim  _ {n \\to \\infty} \\mathbb {E} | X _ {n} | ^ {s} = \\mathbb {E} | X | ^ {s}",
                "math_type": "latex",
                "image_source": {
                    "path": "images/76e371771fa6ea49fc40ef488db9c7c884e6c1c0b0a21c5f15bbd1ec3f02ea17.jpg"
                }
            },
            "bbox": [
                421,
                258,
                573,
                281
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "for all "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "0 < s < r"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ". "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                112,
                300,
                238,
                316
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Problem 2. Let "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "p ( x , y )"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "be the (one-step) transition function of a Markov chain on a discrete state space S and "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "p _ { n } ( x , y )"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "be the "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "n"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ",-step transition function. Show that for any positive integers "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "L"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "and "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "N"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "and any two states "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "x"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "and "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "y"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ",we have "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                111,
                334,
                883,
                383
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "equation_interline",
            "content": {
                "math_content": "\\sum_ {n = L} ^ {N + L} p _ {n} (x, y) \\leq \\sum_ {n = 0} ^ {N} p _ {n} (y, y).",
                "math_type": "latex",
                "image_source": {
                    "path": "images/e519171cbe47f36e2437f8075d9446b8547a79899ecae6a5c742159886c3ae47.jpg"
                }
            },
            "bbox": [
                395,
                383,
                599,
                426
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Problem 3. Let "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\{ X _ { n } \\}"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "be an independent, identically distributed sequence of random variables with the symmetric Bernoulli distribution "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                111,
                465,
                883,
                498
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "equation_interline",
            "content": {
                "math_content": "\\mathbb {P} \\left\\{X = 1 \\right\\} = \\mathbb {P} \\left\\{X = - 1 \\right\\} = \\frac {1}{2}.",
                "math_type": "latex",
                "image_source": {
                    "path": "images/79828a3edcde51291e5e6488ba8f3f8db97ec7d0404240beaafd3a2e59ea5202.jpg"
                }
            },
            "bbox": [
                385,
                500,
                606,
                518
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Let "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "S _ { n } = \\sum _ { i = 1 } ^ { N } X _ { i }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "be the partial sum. Show that for all "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\begin{array} { r } { \\alpha > \\frac { 1 } { 2 } } \\end{array}"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ", "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                112,
                536,
                544,
                579
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "equation_interline",
            "content": {
                "math_content": "\\mathbb {P} \\left\\{\\lim  _ {n \\rightarrow \\infty} \\frac {S _ {n}}{n ^ {\\alpha}} = 0 \\right\\} = 1.",
                "math_type": "latex",
                "image_source": {
                    "path": "images/93d861aa960db905af10cc0cf86ae4d2df497549592f856580a7efbc75685916.jpg"
                }
            },
            "bbox": [
                416,
                598,
                576,
                635
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Problem 4. Let "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "X ^ { n } = \\left\\{ X _ { i j } \\right\\}"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "be an "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "n \\times n"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "random matrix whose entries are independent and identically distributed random variables with the symmetric Bernoulli distribution "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                111,
                681,
                883,
                715
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "equation_interline",
            "content": {
                "math_content": "\\mathbb {P} \\left\\{X = 0 \\right\\} = \\mathbb {P} \\left\\{X = 1 \\right\\} = \\frac {1}{2}.",
                "math_type": "latex",
                "image_source": {
                    "path": "images/a79d503f72751f27450ad06a8b2383d7a7cc2fb3645778660e6a0527b0555a58.jpg"
                }
            },
            "bbox": [
                392,
                734,
                601,
                756
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Let "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "p _ { n } = \\mathbb { P }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "{det "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "X _ { N }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "is odd}. Show that "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\operatorname* { l i m } _ { n \\to \\infty } p _ { n } > 0"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ". "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                111,
                773,
                488,
                797
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "title",
            "content": {
                "title_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Part II: Statistics "
                    }
                ],
                "level": 1
            },
            "bbox": [
                112,
                820,
                263,
                835
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Problem 5. You have been asked to help design a randomized trial of a new drug, call it drug A, to be used in place of the current drug, call it drug "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "B"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ", for a particular medical condition. The budget is fixed to have 1000 patients treated with A and 1000 treated with drug "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "B"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ". The issue is how to do the allocation of patients, because we have many pre-randomization measurements on each patient, roughly 200, such as blood pressure "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                111,
                851,
                883,
                919
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "page_header",
            "content": {
                "page_header_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "S.-T. Yau College Student Mathematics Contests 2021 "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                282,
                68,
                712,
                85
            ]
        }
    ],
    [
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "recordings, age, sex, and a large collection of genetics measurements. Obviously it is desirable to have the A group similar to the "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "B"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "group with respect to all pre-treatment covariates and non-linear functions of them that are expected to influence the effectiveness of the drugs with respect to the outcome variables. "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                116,
                71,
                885,
                122
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Complete (or simple) randomization does this in expectation, but with many covariates, some covariates will not be balanced between the "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "A"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "and "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "B"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "groups in any one single randomized allocation. Standard blocking used in traditional experimental design can force balance on a few covariates, but the designer of drug A wants to have an experimental design that creates balance on many covariates, and feels that you, as a modern applied mathematician/statistician, should be able to do this. "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                116,
                133,
                885,
                219
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Describe a class of methods that achieves this goal where each patient has a positive probability of receiving drug A and a positive probability of receiving drug "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "B"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ". Provide enough detail that you are describing an explicit algorithm. "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                116,
                229,
                885,
                279
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Problem 6. You are given the results of a randomized experiment of two drugs, A and "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "B"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ". The experiment was not conducted in the usual way, however, but rather by allocating patients by a machine-learning algorithm under which each patient has a positive probability of receiving A and of receiving "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "B"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "; moreover the algorithm is completely specified and is built to create better than random balance on the covariates. "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                116,
                299,
                885,
                367
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "list",
            "content": {
                "list_type": "text_list",
                "list_items": [
                    {
                        "item_type": "text",
                        "item_content": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "content": "(a) Can unbiased estimates of the causal effect of drug A versus "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "equation_inline",
                                "content": "B"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "content": "be found, and if so, show why. "
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "item_type": "text",
                        "item_content": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "content": "(b) Can exact small sample, non-parametric inferences for the causal effect in part (a) be derived, based solely on the randomization distribution of some statistic? For example, can we find exact significance levels under a sharp null hypothesis? If so, outline how to accomplish this goal. "
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                125,
                377,
                880,
                453
            ]
        }
    ]
]